<TITLE> Sri Lanka confirm India tour schedule </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 COLOMBO, Sri Lanka, March 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Sri Lanka Cricket (SLC) has confirmed that India will tour the island in July and August to play in three tests and five one-day internationals. The six-week tour will includes two test matches in Colombo and one at the newly renovated Galle International Stadium. Two one-day games will be staged in Dambulla and the three remaining games will be day-night matches played at the Premadasa International Stadium in Colombo. Tour schedule: July 18-20 - Warm-up game July 23-27 - First Test (SSC) July 31 to Aug 4 - Second Test (Galle) Aug 8-12 - Third Test (Premadasa) Aug 18 - First ODI (Dambulla) Aug 20 - Second ODI (Dambulla) Aug 24 - Third ODI (Premadasa) - day/night Aug 26 - Fourth ODI (Premadasa) - day/night Aug 29 - Fifth ODI (Premadasa) - day/nig
